---
import Section from "../../ui/Section.astro";
import Container from "../../ui/Container.astro";
import Heading from "../../ui/Heading.astro";
import Text from "../../ui/Text.astro";
import Badge from "../../ui/Badge.astro";
import Button from "../../ui/Button.astro";
import PhoneMockup from "../../react/PhoneMockup";
import TelegramIcon from "../../ui/TelegramIcon.astro";
---

<Section class="relative py-28 overflow-hidden">
  <Container>

    <!-- HEADER -->
    <div class="text-center mb-20">
      <Badge variant="gold" class="mb-4 flex items-center justify-center mx-auto">
        Telegram <TelegramIcon class="w-4 h-4 ml-2 -mt-1" />
      </Badge>

      <Heading level={2} class="mb-4">
        Where the work actually happens
      </Heading>

      <Text muted class="max-w-2xl mx-auto">
        Telegram is not support. It’s not marketing.
        It’s where analysis, execution logic and real-time context live.
      </Text>
    </div>

    <!-- CONTENT -->
    <div class="grid grid-cols-1 lg:grid-cols-2 gap-16 items-center">

      <!-- PHONE / VISUAL -->
      <div class="flex justify-center lg:justify-start">
        <div class="relative translate-x-4">
          <PhoneMockup client:visible />
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- COPY -->
      <div class="flex flex-col gap-6 max-w-xl">

        <Heading level={3}>
          One channel. Clear structure.
        </Heading>

        <Text muted>
          We use Telegram as a real working environment.
          Market context, execution notes and updates are shared openly,
          without promises or artificial urgency.
        </Text>

        <ul class="text-sm text-white/70 space-y-2">
          <li>• Market context & structure</li>
          <li>• Execution reasoning</li>
          <li>• Free & premium environments</li>
        </ul>

        <Text muted class="text-xs">
          Access to groups is managed from the main channel.
          No guarantees. No signals without context.
        </Text>

        <div class="pt-4">
          <Button
            href="https://t.me/ELDORADOFX"
            target="_blank"
          >
            Open Telegram Channel →
          </Button>
        </div>

      </div>

    </div>

  </Container>
</Section>
